with more detail coming in **** Sections X and Y ***.
The first fundamental aspect of lighting is a clear definition of what we mean by \emph{light}.
Light is useful energy in the form of 
electromagnetic (EM) radiation. 
Light energy is quantified in terms of 
energy~($E$),
wavelength~($\lambda$), and
frequency~($\nu$), 
all related by Planck's equation:
%
\begin{equation}
  E = h \nu = \frac{hc}{\lambda} \; ,
\end{equation}
%
where $c$ is the speed of light (in m/s).
